<br>
1- Do you ever wonder why it is they have a "bad rap"?  I mean, call me crazy, but I don't think people just randomly picked a guild to single out as the larger collection of assholes on the server.  I generally judge the person by their actions, but that doesn't prevent me (or others) from just cringing slightly due to past instances where that tag has been trouble.  As you add more and more examples of bad things happening, and no examples of good, you're bound to get a "bad rap" out of the efforts of others.  This then follows your tag, unfair as that may be.  The sour attitude received a lot of the time wasn't just an evil idea hatched by some group of players in a dark, smoke-filled room somewhere.  No conspiracy, just history.<br>
<br>
2- I don't think anyone not associated with ToV gives a rat's ass what y'all are doing.  I know I don't have a ToV speedkey that executes a /who all Tides command.  Why?  I <i>don't</i> give a shit where you are.  I don't care what you are doing.  There is an exception to this rule however.  My lack of concern ends about the time that you do something that affects me.  Welcome to human nature.  I think you'll find this is the case with about anybody.<br>
<br>
To sum it up, in the words of Will Smith, "<i>Don't start nothin', won't be nothin'.</i>" <p>Faust<BR>
